---
permalink: /index.html
---
{%- from "components/picture.njk" import picture -%}
<div class="[ stack ][][]">
	<picture>
		<source
			srcset="/images/desktop@2x.avif"
			media="(orientation:landscape)"
			type="image/avif"
		/>
		<source
			srcset="/images/desktop@2x.jpg"
			media="(orientation:landscape)"
			type="image/jpeg"
		/>
		<source
			srcset="/images/desktop@2x.webp"
			media="(orientation:landscape)"
			type="image/webp"
		/>

		<source
			srcset="/images/mobile@2x.avif"
			media="(orientation:portrait)"
			type="image/avif"
		/>
		<source
			srcset="/images/mobile@2x.webp"
			media="(orientation:portrait)"
			type="image/webp"
		/>
		<source
			srcset="/images/mobile@2x.jpg"
			media="(orientation:portrait)"
			type="image/jpeg"
		/>

		<img
			alt="Spelling Bee puzzle with Spell Check visible."
			src="/images/desktop@2x.jpg"
		/>
	</picture>

	<div class="[ stack-sm ][ inset ][]">
		<p>Whether you’re new to the Spelling Bee or an old pro, sometimes it’s nice to peek at how close you are to the finish line.</p>
		<p>Spell Check makes it quick and easy to see how many words you have left in today’s puzzle.</p>
	</div>
</div>

<aside class="[ stack-xs ][][ reminder ]">
	<h2 class="[][][ reminder__heading ]">Please Note</h2>
	<p><span class="[][ nowrap ][]">{{ metadata.site.title }}</span> is made and maintained by <a href="https://ashur.cab/rera">Ashur Cabrera</a>, and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the <span class="[][ nowrap ][]">New York Times</span>.</p>
</aside>

<section
	class="[ stack-sm ][ inset ][ section ]"
	id="usage"
>
	<h2 class="[][][ section__heading ]">How it works</h2>
	<p>After <a href="#install">installing</a> the {{ metadata.site.title }} bookmarklet, open the <a href="https://nytimes.com/puzzles/spelling-bee">Spelling Bee</a> in your web browser.</p>
	<p>Any time you need a hint or want to see your progress, click or tap the bookmarklet. No need to switch tabs to check a different page: {{ metadata.site.title }} will appear right in front of your puzzle.</p>

	<h3 class="[][][ section__subheading ]">Reading the grid</h3>
	<p>The {{ metadata.site.title }} grid shows the number of words remaining for each letter.</p>
	<p>For example, a <strong>2</strong> in the <strong>7</strong> column of row <strong>G</strong> means two more 7-letter words that start with “G” are left.</p>

	{{ picture(
		{
			alt: "Spell Check grid showing two remaining 7-letter words that begin with G.",
			src: "/images/grid-highlight@2x.jpg",
			height: 543,
			width: 1168
		}
	) }}

	<p class="[][][ usage__check ]">When you’ve found every accepted solution for a given letter and length, a green checkmark lets you know there are no words left to uncover</p>
</section>

<section
	class="[ stack ][ inset ][ section ]"
	id="install"
>
	<header class="[ stack-xs ][][]">
		<h2 class="[][][ section__heading ]">Get started</h2>
		<p>{{ metadata.site.title }} is supported by most modern web browsers and operating systems, including those listed below.</p>
	</header>

	<ul
		aria-label="Accordion Control Button Group"
		class="[ stack-xs ][ accordion ][ install__categories ]"
	>
		<li class="[][][ install__category ]">
			<h3 class="[][][ install__heading ]">
				<button
					aria-controls="install-android"
					aria-expanded="false"
					class="install__button"
				>
					<span><strong>Android</strong> (Chrome)</span>
				</button>
			</h3>
			<div
				aria-hidden="true"
				class="[ stack-sm ][][ install__content ]"
				id="install-android"
			>
				<ol class="[ stack-xs ][][ install__steps ]">
					<li>Copy the bookmarklet below</li>
					<li>Tap Chrome’s overflow button, located on the right side of the toolbar</li>
					<li>Tap the star icon to create a new bookmark</li>
					<li>Tap <strong>Edit</strong> in the “Bookmarked” alert that briefly appears above Chrome’s toolbar</li>
					<li>Delete the original URL</li>
					<li>Paste the bookmarklet from step 1</li>
					<li>Tap the back button to save your changes</li>
				</ol>

				<div class="[ stack-sm ][][]">
					<h4>Using bookmarklets in Chrome</h4>

					<ol class="[ stack-xs ][][ install__steps ]">
						<li>Tap Chrome’s URL bar</li>
						<li>Begin typing “spellcheck”</li>
						<li>Tap the bookmarklet in the search results</li>
					</ol>

					{{ picture(
						{
							alt: "The Chrome URL bar with 'spell check' partially entered, and the bookmarklet visible in the results",
							src: "/images/android@2x.jpg",
							height: 543,
							width: 1170
						}
					) }}
				</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li class="[][][ install__category ]">
			<h3 class="[][][ install__heading ]">
				<button
					aria-controls="install-desktop"
					aria-expanded="false"
					class="install__button"
				>
					<span><strong>Desktop</strong> (Chrome, Firefox, Safari)</span>
				</button>
			</h3>
			<div
				aria-hidden="true"
				class="[][][ install__content ]"
				id="install-desktop"
			>
				<ol class="[ stack-xs ][][ install__steps ]">
					<li>Open your browser’s bookmarks toolbar</li>
					<li>Click and drag this <a class="[][][ install__bookmarklet ]" href="{{ bookmarklet | safe }}">{{ metadata.site.title }}</a> to the toolbar</li>
				</ol>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li class="[][][ install__category ]">
			<h3 class="[][][ install__heading ]">
				<button
					aria-controls="install-ios"
					aria-expanded="false"
					class="install__button"
				>
					<span><strong>iOS</strong> (Safari)</span>
				</button>
			</h3>
			<div
				aria-hidden="true"
				id="install-ios"
				class="[ stack ][][ install__content ]"
			>
				<ol class="[ stack-xs ][][ install__steps ]">
					<li>Copy the bookmarklet below</li>
					<li>Tap the Share icon in Safari’s toolbar</li>
					<li>Tap <strong>Add Bookmark</strong></li>
					<li>Tap <strong>Save</strong></li>
					<li>Tap the Bookmarks icon in Safari’s toolbar</li>
					<li>Tap <strong>Edit</strong></li>
					<li>Tap the <strong>Spell Check</strong> bookmark</li>
					<li>Delete the original URL</li>
					<li>Paste the bookmarklet from step 1</li>
					<li>Tap <strong>Done</strong> three times to save your changes</li>
				</ol>
			</div>
		</li>
	</ul>

	<div class="[ stack-xs ][][ install__copy ]">
		<label for=""bookmarklet-ios">Bookmarklet</label>
		<input
			id="bookmarklet-ios"
			onfocus="this.select()"
			type="text"
			value="{{ bookmarklet | safe }}"
		>
	</div>
</section>
